=========================================
C++ STL MAP – INTERVIEW NOTES
=========================================

1. What is map?
----------------
map is an associative container that stores data in key-value pairs.

Example:
map<int, string> m;
m[1] = "A";
m[2] = "B";

Output:
1 -> A
2 -> B

-----------------------------------------
2. Key Properties
-----------------
- Stores key-value pairs
- Keys are UNIQUE
- Automatically sorted by key (ascending)
- Implemented using Red-Black Tree
- Time complexity: O(log n)

-----------------------------------------
3. Internal Implementation
--------------------------
map is implemented using Red-Black Tree (Self-balancing BST)

- Maintains sorted order
- Guarantees O(log n) operations
- Height = O(log n)

Interview Answer:
map uses Red-Black Tree which keeps data sorted and balanced.

-----------------------------------------
4. Complexity
--------------
insert    O(log n)
erase     O(log n)
find      O(log n)
access[]  O(log n)
size      O(1)

-----------------------------------------
5. Important Functions
----------------------
insert()
erase()
